
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    `m2300w-wrapper` yek dastoor ya package narmafzari ast baraye rah andazi va control-e printer-haye Samsung M2300W dar system-haye Linux. In komak mikonad ta printer be dorosti kar konad va shoma betavanid chaph konid.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹  Be tore mostaghim dar terminal estefade nemishavad.  In yek wrapper script ast ke dar posht-e sahne kar mikonad.  
    🔹  Baraye estefade az printer, bayad driver-haye munasib va PPD file ra install konid. (PPD file tarif mikonad che tor printer shoma kar mikonad).

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ sudo apt install printer-driver-splix  
    
    🔹  Install kardane driver-haye lazem baraye printer-haye Samsung. (Dar Debian/Ubuntu)

    $ sudo systemctl restart cups  
    
    🔹  Restart kardane service CUPS (Common Unix Printing System) baraye shenakhtane printer.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    Ba'd az install kardane driver-ha, bayad az system setting-haye Linux (mesle Ubuntu) printer-e khod ra ezafe konid va model Samsung M2300W ra entekhab konid.  `m2300w-wrapper` dar posht-e sahne kar mikonad ta komak konad chaph be dorosti anjam shavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    `m2300w-wrapper` is a command or software package used to enable and control Samsung M2300W printers on Linux systems. It helps the printer to function correctly and allows you to print.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 It's generally not used directly from the terminal. It is a wrapper script that works in the background.
    🔹 To use the printer, you need to install the appropriate drivers and PPD file (PPD file defines how your printer works).

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ sudo apt install printer-driver-splix
    
    🔹 Installing necessary drivers for Samsung printers. (On Debian/Ubuntu)

    $ sudo systemctl restart cups
    
    🔹 Restarting the CUPS (Common Unix Printing System) service to recognize the printer.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    After installing the drivers, you need to add your printer via the Linux system settings (such as in Ubuntu) and select the Samsung M2300W model. `m2300w-wrapper` works in the background to help ensure printing works correctly.

